Comment:
As a resident living within 200 yards of the site, I wish to object to this application on the following
grounds:
Increased traffic and road safety risks: 70 plus vehicles could park on nearby roads with up to 80
extra vehicles vehicles locally during the overlap;
School safety: Avenue Primary School has more than 1,000 pupils. Extra traffic / parking
increases risk at drop off / pickup and reduces visibility;
Serious noise and late night disturbance: dispersal of up to 250 people at 11 pm can mean voices,
engines, doors slamming, and cars circling for space;
Vulnerable residents: a nearby care home and elderly residents are hardest hit by obstruction and
late night disturbance;
Visually overbearing and completely out of character: the proposed extensions and increased
building height would create a structure that is visually dominant and entirely out of keeping with
the domestic scale of neighbouring properties.
